5, \"rank\": 0.022759771661909137, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pitch invaders are detained by stewards after the match.\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS/Thaier Al-Sudani    PublishedJul 25, 2024, 07:25 PM  UpdatedJul 25, 2024, 08:10 PM  PARIS - Chaos descended on Argentina's opening men's soccer match and a spying scandal engulfed the women's soccer tournament in an inauspicious opening day of sport at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 553, \"end\": 562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9487285245238495, \"rank\": 0.05402792803395387, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's what you need to know about the Paris Games on Thursday, the day before the Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SOCCER \\\"CIRCUS\\\"  Argentina soccer coach Javier Mascherano slammed the chaotic conclusion of his side's opening game against Morocco, branding it \\\"the biggest circus I have ever seen in my life.\\\"\", \"from\": 818, \"to\": 1012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 835, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9487285245238495, \"rank\": 0.05402792803395387, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 858, \"end\": 875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javier_Mascherano\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Javier Mascherano\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javier_Mascherano\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javier_Mascherano\"}, {\"begin\": 942, \"end\": 949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9996556527205858, \"rank\": 0.00023556359997218006, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Argentina thought it had salvaged a draw deep into additional time before the goal was dramatically ruled out for offside by the VAR and a pitch invasion forced play to be suspended for nearly two hours.\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1217, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1014, \"end\": 1023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9487285245238495, \"rank\": 0.05402792803395387, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1143, \"end\": 1146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.2795081170080686e-13, \"text\": \"VAR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What happened on the pitch was a scandal, it's not a neighbourhood tournament, it's the Olympics,\\\" Mascherano told reporters.\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'DRONEGATE'  Women's soccer was reeling after New Zealand said their Canadian rivals had flown a drone over a training session, engulfing the tournament in a spying scandal.\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1393, \"end\": 1404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6501009953716794, \"rank\": 0.37750154645489614, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1416, \"end\": 1424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9985690326958643, \"rank\": 0.0013441244180541533, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Global soccer's governing body FIFA began disciplinary proceedings and Canada Soccer said it would launch an independent review, as coach Bev Priestman stepped down from opening match duties.\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1553, \"end\": 1557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0265757297684268e-14, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\"}, {\"begin\": 1593, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canada Soccer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1660, \"end\": 1673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bev Priestman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Priestman apologised and said the buck stopped with her.\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"New Zealand Football CEO Andrew Pragnell told FIFA on Thursday to take urgent action to address it.\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1872, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1773, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Football\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Zealand Football\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Football\"}, {\"begin\": 1819, \"end\": 1823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0265757297684268e-14, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ANTI-DOPING WARS  Relations between the World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) and U.S. Anti-Doping Agency (USADA) have taken another turn for the worse over a long running dispute concerning the global body's handling of a case involving 23 Chinese swimmers.\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 2126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1914, \"end\": 1945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 1975, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"beg