sentence\": \"In April, the New York Times and German broadcaster ARD revealed that 23 Chinese swimmers tested positive for banned heart medication trimetazidine (TMZ) at a training camp in 2021 but still competed at the Tokyo Olympics Games that year.\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2350, \"end\": 2358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999886951534418, \"rank\": 1.1289902904773058e-05, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 2369, \"end\": 2375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9996043211685324, \"rank\": 0.0002989467381448114, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2388, \"end\": 2391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Das_Erste\", \"score\": 0.9999999998749445, \"rank\": 1.2485958583863226e-10, \"text\": \"ARD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Das_Erste\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Das_Erste\"}, {\"begin\": 2409, \"end\": 2416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9703108712499429, \"rank\": 0.030584133873327615, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USADA chief Travis Tygart has publicly accused WADA of a cover-up.\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2576, \"end\": 2581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Travis Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. law enforcement has now taken up the case and could take action using the American Rodchenkov Anti-Doping Act.\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 2758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2643, \"end\": 2647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9386823939619617, \"rank\": 0.057573340531099214, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2722, \"end\": 2730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999804459, \"rank\": 1.6468845686183404e-11, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2731, \"end\": 2741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grigory_Rodchenkov\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rodchenkov\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grigory_Rodchenkov\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grigory_Rodchenkov\"}, {\"begin\": 2754, \"end\": 2757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Act_of_Parliament\", \"score\": 0.8563408752903029, \"rank\": 0.12915538716708747, \"text\": \"Act\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Act_of_Parliament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Act_of_Parliament\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA says the United States is taking a unilateral approach to anti-doping rules that risked undermining global rules.\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2774, \"end\": 2787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9986948441402743, \"rank\": 0.0012204476467234957, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USADA told Reuters that WADA's move to take the U.S. to the CRC was retaliatory.\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 2960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2880, \"end\": 2885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 2891, \"end\": 2898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8494506191063586e-20, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 2940, \"end\": 2943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Convention_on_the_Rights_of_the_Child\", \"score\": 0.9999999708934415, \"rank\": 1.7180795239753004e-08, \"text\": \"CRC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Convention_on_the_Rights_of_the_Child\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Convention_on_the_Rights_of_the_Child\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SECURITY  France will roll out its largest post-war security operation at Friday's official Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 3071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2972, \"end\": 2978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.977212580116715, \"rank\": 0.022759771661909137, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3054, \"end\": 3070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999911912547377, \"rank\": 5.63166528192871e-06, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An iron curtain has descended across central Paris as police impose a security perimeter along the banks of the River Seine.\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3117, \"end\": 3122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.037456477612603e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3184, \"end\": 3195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Security officials say as many as 45,000 police and thousands of soldiers and private security guards will be tasked with securing the ceremony and sporting events that will be spread across the French capital.\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3393, \"end\": 3399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8897633935467955, \"rank\": 0.0638458596089587, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the few operational bridges in central Paris across the Seine was briefly shut down on Thursday morning, as police conducte